<CENTER><H2><FONT SIZE = +3>T</FONT>he  <FONT SIZE = +3>H</FONT>eritage  <FONT SIZE = +3>F</FONT>oundation</H2> </CENTER>

<CENTER><H3><FONT SIZE = +2>P</FONT>ublications <FONT SIZE = +2>L</FONT>ibrary</H3> 

<HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 50%>
<P>
<B> Crime and Law: Crime and Violence</B>
</CENTER>
<ul><P>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt4.html">What the 104th Congress Did to Combat Crime</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moffit.htm">Robert E. Moffit</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)
<br>
<a href="/heritage/issues96/chpt8.html">Crime</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/fagan.htm">Patrick F. Fagan</a> and <a href="/heritage/staff/moffit.htm">Robert E. Moffit</a>.  (<i>Issues '96: The Candidate's Briefing Book</i>)<p>
<p>

<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>10/28/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/crimelaw/bg1097.html">How State and Local Officials Can Combat Violent Juvenile Crime</a>  by James Wootton and Robert O. Heck. (State Backgrounder #1097/S)

<li>10/20/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/bgup281.html">LIUNA, Organized Crime, and the Clinton Administration</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/weinstein.html">Kenneth R. Weinstein</a> and August Stofferahn. (Backgrounder Update #281)
<li>10/15/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/crimelaw/lect573.html">Cutting Crime and Restoring Order: What America Can Learn from New York's Finest</a> by William J. Bratton. (Lecture #573) 
<li>9/1/96 <a href="/heritage/p_review/sept96/cal.html">Out of Order</a> By Steven G. Calabresi. (September-October 1996, Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship)
<li>9/1/96 <a href="/heritage/p_review/sept96/portman.html">Addicted to Failure</a> by Representative Rob Portman. (September-October 1996, Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship)
<li>8/21/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/crimelaw/bg1089b.html">Getting Backup: Twenty-One Steps Public Officials Can Take To Support Their Local Police</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moffit.htm">Robert E. Moffit</a> and <a href="/heritage/staff/meese.htm">Edwin Meese III</a>. (Backgrounder No. 1089)

<li>8/19/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/crimelaw/fyi117.html">What the 104th Congress Did to Combat Crime</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moffit.htm">Robert E. Moffit</a>. (F.Y.I. #117)
